    <preamble>
      <formula name="enactingFormula" eId="formula_1">
        <p xml:space="preserve">
          <span class="italic">The General Assembly</span>,</p>
      </formula>
      <container name="Recalling" eId="container_2">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recalling</span> the purposes and principles of the Charter of the United Nations,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Underlining" eId="container_3">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Underlining</span> the important role and comparative advantage of an adequately resourced, relevant, coherent, efficient and effective United Nations system in promoting international cooperation,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Recalling" eId="container_4">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recalling</span> the role of the Secretary-General as the chief administrative officer of the Organization, in accordance with Article 97 of the Charter,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Recognizing" eId="container_5">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recognizing</span> the central role of Member States in the reform process, which should be inclusive and transparent,</p>
      </container>
    </preamble>
    <mainBody>
      <paragraph eId="para_6" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>1.</num>
        <content eId="para_6__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Welcomes</span> the efforts of the Secretary-General to strengthen the United Nations in order to keep pace with a changing world and to make it fit for the present and future challenges;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_7" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>2.</num>
        <content eId="para_7__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Looks forward</span> to receiving, in accordance with established procedures, the relevant proposals of the Secretary-General in the framework of his UN80 initiative, taking into account the necessity to have clearly defined objectives and an evidence-based approach, and aiming at strengthening the impact of the United Nations and enhancing its agility, responsiveness and resilience while addressing the issue of duplicative efforts and ensuring effective and efficient mandate delivery across all three pillars of the work of the United Nations;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_9" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>3.</num>
        <content eId="para_9__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Calls upon</span> the entities and specialized agencies of the United Nations system to align their reform efforts with this approach, as appropriate. </p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
    </mainBody>
